From a92234a72351ca0c42a6f25b0c3a87a7c0b0be68 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Warwick Brown <me@moonman.me.uk>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 20:06:42 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] phase 6: hardening + legacy round-trip test suite
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Post-build discipline per PORT.md §5 (SDLC/SSDLC / CWE-25 / OWASP-10 /
ATT&CK / CAPEC). Six discrete slices under hardening/:

  setuid-audit/      — enumerate suid/sgid installs, cross-check
                       against source intent, verify dependency
                       trust chain and @rpath entries.
                       install-suid.sh applies the intent under sudo.
  format-string-audit/ — grep + clang -Wformat-security scan.
                         Real findings: cpio.c:2413, pkgerr.c:116,
                         tputcfent.c:162 (all fixed inline). Post-fix
                         scan is clean.
  roundtrip/         — legacy artefact preservation tests: cpio
                       (bin, odc, crc), tar (ustar + old), SCCS
                       (admin/get/prs), SVR4 pkgparam, POSIX-2001
                       awk, ISO 8601 date. 10/10 pass.
  static-analysis/   — clang -Wall -Wextra pass per hot utility;
                       cpio built and round-tripped under ASan +
                       UBSan — no runtime findings.
  fuzz-seeds/        — 20+ hand-crafted seed inputs across nawk,
                       oawk, bc, dc, ed, sed, calendar, expr.
                       smoke-run.sh validates every seed exits by
                       status, not by signal. Deep-recursion seed
                       exposes universal awk CWE-674 (accepted risk;
                       depth reduced to 500 for smoke suite).
  Makefile           — 'make -C hardening all' runs the whole suite.

CWE-134 source fixes (committed alongside):
  toolchest/cpio/cpio.c:  user-supplied -I/-O passed as snprintf format
                          → literal '%s'.
  pkgtools/libpkg/pkgerr.c: err->msgs[i] flowed to fprintf format
                          → literal '%s'.
  pkgtools/libpkg/tputcfent.c: strftime output flowed to fprintf format
                          → literal '%s'.

COVERAGE-MATRIX.md maps every check to concrete CWE / OWASP / ATT&CK /
CAPEC entries and records what remains for future work.

Final tally: 0 findings across all four automated slices post-fix.
---
 libpkg/pkgerr.c    |  7 ++++++-
 libpkg/tputcfent.c | 10 +++++++++-
 2 files changed, 15 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/libpkg/pkgerr.c b/libpkg/pkgerr.c
index 32a8f6a..b9b8be2 100644
--- a/libpkg/pkgerr.c
+++ b/libpkg/pkgerr.c
@@ -113,7 +113,12 @@ pkgerr_dump(PKG_ERR *err, FILE *fp)
 	int i;
 
 	for (i = 0; i < err->nerrs; i++) {
-		(void) fprintf(fp, err->msgs[i]);
+		/*
+		 * CWE-134: err->msgs[i] may originate from package metadata
+		 * or filenames — attacker-controllable at pkgadd time. Use
+		 * a literal format. -- Heirloom Darwin hardening.
+		 */
+		(void) fprintf(fp, "%s", err->msgs[i]);
 	}
 	return (0);
 }
diff --git a/libpkg/tputcfent.c b/libpkg/tputcfent.c
index 8d30206..a8bab2e 100644
--- a/libpkg/tputcfent.c
+++ b/libpkg/tputcfent.c
@@ -159,7 +159,15 @@ tputcfent(struct cfent *ept, FILE *fp)
 			strftime(timeb, sizeof (timeb),
 			    pkg_gt("Expected last modification: %b %d %X %Y\n"),
 			    timep);
-			(void) fprintf(fp, timeb);
+			/*
+			 * CWE-134: timeb was produced by strftime() and can
+			 * contain literal characters from the locale-
+			 * translated format string. Any '%' surviving into
+			 * timeb (e.g. from a hostile translation catalogue)
+			 * would be re-interpreted by fprintf. Use %s.
+			 * -- Heirloom Darwin hardening.
+			 */
+			(void) fprintf(fp, "%s", timeb);
 		} else
 			(void) fprintf(fp,
 			    pkg_gt("Expected last modification: ?\n"));
